<div id="review_3805364633" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3805364633" />
    <a title="Trey Smith" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/52709676-trey-smith"><img alt="Trey Smith" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1477045871p2/52709676.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3805364633?book_show_action=true">Jun 13, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Trey Smith" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Trey Smith" href="/user/show/52709676-trey-smith">Trey Smith</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3805364633" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14942393543512741260">Foote provides a masterful narrative of the various campaigns between the Winter of 1962 up to the Spring of 1964 in this second book of his Civil War narrative. Amazing the swing of momentum as Lee routs the Union army with inferior numbers but great strategic position at Fredericksburg then does the same by splitting his Army with General Jackson outflanking the Union left at Chancellorsville. However the aftermath of that victory resulting in the friendly fire shooting of Jackson begins a sea</span>
  <span id="freeText14942393543512741260" style="display:none">Foote provides a masterful narrative of the various campaigns between the Winter of 1962 up to the Spring of 1964 in this second book of his Civil War narrative. Amazing the swing of momentum as Lee routs the Union army with inferior numbers but great strategic position at Fredericksburg then does the same by splitting his Army with General Jackson outflanking the Union left at Chancellorsville. However the aftermath of that victory resulting in the friendly fire shooting of Jackson begins a season of detrimental setbacks and losses for the South. Vicksburg is besieged and taken followed shortly by Port Hudson, Lee fails in his offensive actions at Gettysburg resulting in retreat, and though a frustrating victory is had in the West at Chickamagua, Bragg is defeated in his seige of Chattanooga losing that vital Southern city and also his command. Foote provides insightful first hand accounts of correspondence of commanders and those of privates to show a real life picture of this war. It is a masterpiece and I highly recommend it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14942393543512741260" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


